  "instructions": [
    "Cut the lamb shoulder into 1-inch cubes and season with salt and black pepper.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large copper mug over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the lamb cubes and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic, ginger, and flour and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Pour in the lamb stock and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes.",
    "Stir in the fresh lemon and lime juice and cook for an additional 2 minutes.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg whites and a pinch of salt until frothy.",
    "Add the egg whites to the lamb mixture and stir to combine.",
    "Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes, until the eggs are set.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh parsley and a sprinkle of lemon and lime zest.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
  ],
